cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of web crawled videos for weakly supervised learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to retrieve relevant videos, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques to learn from weakly supervised data suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to retrieve relevant videos, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
